# Electron-builder packaged-app output. Per-build ~400MB (AppImage 115MB +
# unpacked linux-unpacked/ tree). Recreate via `pnpm dist`.
electron/release/

# TypeScript incremental-build cache. Mtime-only tracking; re-dirtied on
# every typecheck so committing it creates endless noise diffs. Safe to
# delete — tsc regenerates on next build.
*.tsbuildinfo

# Bleepforge data/ — derived caches + machine-specific user state.
#
# The seven game-domain folders below are a JSON cache rebuilt from the
# Godot project's .tres files on every server boot, kept in sync by the
# live watcher, and pushed back to .tres on every save. Tracking them in
# git produced merge-conflict churn on every save without adding value
# (the .tres files inside the Godot project are the source of truth).
#
# data/preferences.json carries the Godot project root path + theme
# settings — machine + user specific, would fight across workstations.
#
# What STAYS tracked:
#   data/concept.json          Bleepforge-only project pitch (authored)
#   data/codex/                Game Codex categories + entries (authored)
#   data/help/                 In-app help library (authored)
#   data/dialogs/*/_layout.json  Per-folder graph node positions (authored)
#
# Negation rule keeps _layout.json visible alongside the ignored cache
# JSONs inside data/dialogs/<folder>/. Pattern order matters — the
# negation must come AFTER the broader ignore.
data/dialogs/**/*.json
!data/dialogs/**/_layout.json
data/quests/
data/items/
data/karma/
data/npcs/
data/factions/
data/balloons/
data/preferences.json
